div.h2: Process State Machine Ready Running Blocked

p.em: Preemptive round-robin kernel every transition annotated with trigger + kernel code

div.p: CREATED process_create() kmalloc PCB kmalloc kernel stack (8 KB) fabricate initial context set EFLAGS = 0x202 (IF=1) state = PROCESS_READY
READY In the run queue PCB in circular list kernel stack cold context.esp valid page_directory set ticks_remaining reset
RUNNING On the CPU current_process = this CR3 = page_directory (phys) TSS.ESP0 = kernel_stack_top total_ticks++ per tick CPL = 0 (kernel) or 3 (user)
BLOCKED Awaiting event removed from run queue state = PROCESS_BLOCKED kernel stack suspended NOT selected by scheduler wakeup registered in event source (kbd/timer)
TERMINATED PROCESS_DEAD removed from list kmalloc memory freed page_directory freed kernel stack freed scheduler bypasses
Transition Legend Green arrow = creation / admission Blue arrow = scheduling dispatch Red arrow = preemption Yellow arrow = blocking / wakeup Purple arrow = termination

push EBX, ESI, EDI, EBP pushfd ; save IF flag mov [old+16], ESP ; old->context.esp identity swap mov ESP, [new+16] ; new->context.esp now on new stack popfd ; IF restored (=1) pop EBP, EDI, ESI, EBX ret ; new->EIP

text.tspan: pushfd / push EBX ESI EDI EBP
popfd / pop EBP EDI ESI EBX / ret
Trigger: PIT IRQ0 fires at 100 Hz
